Interface ITargetReport

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    TargetReport

    public interface ITargetReport
    This interface provides information about the ITarget

      • getDefinitionNames

        Set<String> getDefinitionNames()
        Gets the list of all the top-level, externally-visible definitions in the ITarget. The sequence represents the order in which the definitions are exported to the frame. If the compilation did not generate a movie, this method returns an empty collection.
        Returns:
        A collection of definition names.

      • getRequiredRSLs

        List<RSLSettings> getRequiredRSLs()
        Gets the list of all RSLs required to run this application. The list is in the order the RSLs will be loaded. This list does not include legacy RSLs specified using -runtime-shared-libraries. Those RSLs are always required.
        Returns:
        list of RSLs required by the target.

      • getBackgroundColor

        Gets the background color.
        Returns:

      • getWidth

        int getWidth()
        Gets the user-defined width.
        Returns:
        Width of the application, in pixels. 0 if it was not specified.

      • getHeight

        int getHeight()
        Gets the user-defined height.
        Returns:

      • getWidthPercent

        double getWidthPercent()
        Gets the user-defined width percentage.
        Returns:

      • getHeightPercent

        Returns:
